1
00:00:33,595 --> 00:00:40,049
False King, God
has no mercy on you.

2
00:00:41,385 --> 00:00:48,357
He shall fester you with boils
spawned by your many sins.

3
00:00:53,248 --> 00:00:59,285
A child born in Israel will be
a far greater king than you.

4
00:01:00,672 --> 00:01:05,374
He is born to destroy you
and those of your seed.

5
00:01:07,045 --> 00:01:11,714
God's wrath has come upon you.

6
00:01:11,766 --> 00:01:13,549
Agh!

7
00:01:16,387 --> 00:01:20,857
Agh, agh, agh.

8
00:01:23,528 --> 00:01:24,894
Agh!

9
00:01:24,946 --> 00:01:26,229
Agh!

10
00:01:26,281 --> 00:01:27,596
Agh!

11
00:01:27,649 --> 00:01:28,731
Did you see him?

12
00:01:28,783 --> 00:01:30,032
Did you see Isaiah?

13
00:01:30,101 --> 00:01:31,267
Did you see him?

14
00:01:31,319 --> 00:01:32,401
Did you see him?

15
00:01:32,470 --> 00:01:33,335
- Aahh.
- Fa... father

16
00:01:33,388 --> 00:01:35,331
...father it's me,
Antipas.

17
00:01:38,493 --> 00:01:39,575
Antipas,

18
00:01:44,883 --> 00:01:47,500
Wake the priests of the
Sanhedrin.

19
00:01:47,585 --> 00:01:48,801
Very well father.

20
00:01:48,887 --> 00:01:50,720
Now.

21
00:01:50,788 --> 00:01:51,971
I will see them now.

22
00:01:55,226 --> 00:01:59,128
Does your
majesty value truth?

23
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:04,734
For there is harsh
truth in your dream.

24
00:02:04,802 --> 00:02:06,152
I will hear it.

25
00:02:06,237 --> 00:02:11,324
To step beyond these
walls is to know King Herod

26
00:02:11,409 --> 00:02:12,575
is despised.

27
00:02:13,611 --> 00:02:16,362
The zealots denounce
you as a puppet.

28
00:02:16,447 --> 00:02:18,664
Enthroned by the Roman Emperor

29
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,616
against the will of the Jewish
people.

30
00:02:20,668 --> 00:02:23,119
Zealots cannot
enter my father's dreams.

31
00:02:23,171 --> 00:02:27,290
Unless
endowed by sorcery.

32
00:02:27,342 --> 00:02:28,490
Sorcery.

33
00:02:28,543 --> 00:02:30,293
You did
not see Isaiah.

34
00:02:33,965 --> 00:02:37,967
You saw a spectre, a figment.

35
00:02:38,019 --> 00:02:39,468
Figment.

36
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:44,340
The creation
of a sorcerer's skill.

37
00:02:44,392 --> 00:02:48,861
But through prayer
it can be vanquished.

38
00:02:48,947 --> 00:02:51,814
You are a warrior king.

39
00:02:51,866 --> 00:02:54,867
Your voice can make
a vapor of phantoms.

40
00:02:54,953 --> 00:02:56,362
Yes.

41
00:02:58,623 --> 00:02:59,655
A vapor.

42
00:02:59,707 --> 00:03:02,124
Come to the temple.

43
00:03:02,193 --> 00:03:07,363
Through prayer your strength
will grow ever greater.

44
00:03:39,330 --> 00:03:41,730
Well done.

45
00:03:41,783 --> 00:03:44,917
To vanquish phantoms he prays.

46
00:03:45,003 --> 00:03:46,619
Whatever his faults,

47
00:03:46,704 --> 00:03:49,505
a bond between the throne and
temple serves order.

48
00:03:49,573 --> 00:03:52,792
And order serves the
preservation of our people.

49
00:03:57,849 --> 00:03:58,931
Follow me...

50
00:04:07,558 --> 00:04:08,607
Get down...

51
00:04:12,897 --> 00:04:13,963
Greetings.

52
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:16,816
Greetings my...
Greetings sir.

53
00:04:28,162 --> 00:04:31,464
Father, the nobles
who are served by these men

54
00:04:31,549 --> 00:04:33,582
offer you gifts from the
land of the Hind.

55
00:04:36,637 --> 00:04:38,387
What do they
say of their masters?

56
00:04:38,456 --> 00:04:41,257
That they are
from beyond Parthia.

57
00:04:41,309 --> 00:04:44,760
Wanting what of me?

58
00:04:44,812 --> 00:04:47,012
They ask that you hear from their
own lips of their purpose.

59
00:04:48,182 --> 00:04:49,598
Arrange
entertainments.

60
00:05:09,871 --> 00:05:11,537
Majesty,

61
00:05:11,622 --> 00:05:14,156
an alignment of the stars has
drawn us here.

62
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:16,675
These stars.

63
00:05:16,761 --> 00:05:18,210
They foretell a great event.

64
00:05:18,296 --> 00:05:19,595
A child.

65
00:05:19,663 --> 00:05:23,165
Born in your kingdom is
the God of Israel's chosen.

66
00:05:23,217 --> 00:05:24,383
The Messiah.

67
00:05:24,469 --> 00:05:25,801
Messiah?

68
00:05:25,853 --> 00:05:27,553
A King of
the Davidic line to restore

69
00:05:27,638 --> 00:05:30,806
the glory of Israel, as in
the prophecy of Isaiah.

70
00:05:30,858 --> 00:05:31,992
Isaiah.

71
00:05:35,029 --> 00:05:36,123
G...!

72
00:05:39,350 --> 00:05:41,016
Of all the infant boys in
my kingdom

73
00:05:41,068 --> 00:05:44,069
how will you find this one child

74
00:05:44,155 --> 00:05:46,022
destined to be the Messiah?

75
00:05:46,090 --> 00:05:47,356
Knowledge
that the day and time

76
00:05:47,408 --> 00:05:50,910
of his birth match the
position of the stars.

77
00:05:50,995 --> 00:05:53,796
And the child will
give us a sign.

78
00:05:53,864 --> 00:05:55,131
What a blessing.

79
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,260
Yes.

80
00:05:59,504 --> 00:06:00,553
Find this child.

81
00:06:03,707 --> 00:06:07,476
Send me news that I may
come and ... venerate him.

82
00:06:09,564 --> 00:06:11,263
I welcome your holy mission.

83
00:06:12,683 --> 00:06:13,826
Majesty.

84
00:07:53,834 --> 00:07:55,984
Joseph?

85
00:07:56,037 --> 00:07:58,003
What is it?

86
00:07:58,089 --> 00:08:02,207
This
attention, adulation of our boy.

87
00:08:02,293 --> 00:08:03,659
We must leave.

88
00:08:03,711 --> 00:08:05,678
Leave? Why?

89
00:08:05,763 --> 00:08:07,663
Herod.

90
00:08:07,715 --> 00:08:10,099
No king allows a
rival to his throne.

91
00:08:10,167 --> 00:08:11,634
- But our home?
- Enough!

92
00:08:15,473 --> 00:08:16,777
I know what I feel.

93
00:08:18,359 --> 00:08:19,975
You're leaving?

94
00:08:20,027 --> 00:08:21,560
There's danger here.

95
00:08:21,646 --> 00:08:23,028
Where will you go?

96
00:08:23,114 --> 00:08:24,280
Wherever Herod is not.

97
00:08:26,850 --> 00:08:29,285
Elizabeth,
pack our things.

98
00:08:30,204 --> 00:08:32,187
We will go as well. Go on.

99
00:08:32,239 --> 00:08:35,324
Our purpose was visiting your
cousin and now we have none.

100
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:10,776
On this day,

101
00:09:10,861 --> 00:09:13,162
give no thought to what you do.

102
00:09:13,230 --> 00:09:17,232
By King Herod's order, the
male babies, all of them!

103
00:09:17,284 --> 00:09:19,868
You seven this way,
the rest with me.

104
00:09:20,087 --> 00:09:21,236
In there.

105
00:09:22,072 --> 00:09:23,088
You two there.

106
00:09:24,959 --> 00:09:25,991
Is it a boy?

107
00:09:26,077 --> 00:09:27,092
It's a girl!

108
00:09:27,178 --> 00:09:28,377
Show me.

109
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:30,245
Please.

110
00:09:31,932 --> 00:09:32,981
No.

111
00:09:35,419 --> 00:09:36,518
Where are your children?

112
00:09:36,587 --> 00:09:38,137
No. No. No. Aahh.

113
00:09:38,222 --> 00:09:39,772
No. Aaagghh

114
00:09:42,443 --> 00:09:44,226
Agh!

115
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:58,157
Please, I beg you,
don't kill my son.

116
00:09:58,242 --> 00:09:59,341
AGH!

117
00:10:58,352 --> 00:10:59,518
Who is there?

118
00:11:03,507 --> 00:11:04,523
Antipas?

119
00:11:09,146 --> 00:11:10,946
My heart.

120
00:11:11,014 --> 00:11:15,534
Agh.

121
00:11:15,619 --> 00:11:16,818
... Help me.

122
00:11:16,871 --> 00:11:17,953
Agh.

123
00:11:18,021 --> 00:11:19,288
Agh.

124
00:11:19,356 --> 00:11:20,522
Agh.

125
00:11:20,574 --> 00:11:26,194
Antipas, Anti.., Ant,
Antipas, Antipas...

126
